        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 16 at 10:15PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1015 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Valentine, or 28 miles north of Candelaria, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Valentine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
